# Production Environment Variables for Netlify
# In Netlify Dashboard → Site Settings → Environment Variables, add:

VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-url.herokuapp.com/api

# IMPORTANT: Replace 'your-backend-url.herokuapp.com' with your actual backend URL
# Common backend hosting options:
# - Heroku: https://your-app-name.herokuapp.com/api
# - Railway: https://your-app-name.up.railway.app/api  
# - Render: https://your-app-name.onrender.com/api
# - Vercel: https://your-backend-vercel-app.vercel.app/api

# For now, if you haven't deployed your backend yet, you can temporarily use:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
# But remember to update this with your actual backend URL once deployed!